NOTICE: The cross-domain identity features of the Nylo SDK are protected by
patent-pending claims (U.S. Non-Provisional Patent Application). These features
include, but are not limited to:

  1. Cross-Domain Context Preservation (WTX-1 Protocol)
     - Cross-domain token exchange and verification
     - Identity transfer across unrelated domains without third-party cookies
     - URL fragment and postMessage-based token transport

  2. WaiTag Pseudonymous Identity System
     - Domain-bound pseudonymous identifier generation
     - Multi-layer hierarchical identity storage
     - Cross-domain identity resolution and matching

  3. Encrypted Configuration System
     - AES-GCM encrypted tracking configuration
     - Customer-specific key derivation
     - Domain authorization and allowlisting

  4. Confidence-Weighted Identity Resolution
     - Fingerprint-based cross-domain identity matching
     - Canonical identity selection across domains

IMPORTANT NOTICE: Cross-Domain Features

The cross-domain identity features of this software, including but not limited
to the WTX-1 protocol, WaiTag identity system, cross-domain token exchange,
and encrypted configuration system, are covered by patent-pending claims and
are licensed separately under this Nylo Commercial License.

Use of these features in production environments requires a commercial license.

GRANT OF LICENSE

Subject to the terms of this Agreement, a Commercial License grants the
Licensee a non-exclusive, non-transferable right to use the cross-domain
features of the Nylo SDK in production environments.

COMMERCIAL USE DEFINITION

"Commercial Use" means any use of the cross-domain features in connection with:
  (a) A product or service offered to third parties (whether paid or free)
  (b) Internal business operations processing more than 10,000 events per month
  (c) Integration into proprietary analytics, tracking, or personalization
      platforms

PERMITTED FREE USE

The following uses of cross-domain features do NOT require a commercial license:
  (a) Personal, non-commercial projects
  (b) Academic research and educational purposes
  (c) Evaluation and testing in non-production environments
  (d) Open-source projects with fewer than 10,000 monthly events
  (e) Contributing improvements back to the Nylo open-source project

RESTRICTIONS

Without a Commercial License, Licensees may NOT:
  (a) Use cross-domain features in production for commercial purposes
  (b) Sublicense, sell, or redistribute the cross-domain features as part
      of a competing analytics or tracking product
  (c) Remove or modify patent notices, license headers, or attribution
      requirements from the source code
  (d) Claim ownership of the patent-pending technology

